HINT — Level 3: Writable Host-Mounted Script

When a file from the host is bind-mounted into a container,
writes to that file inside the container modify the real file
on the host. If a host process executes that file on a schedule,
you can inject commands that run outside the container.

Look at what's in /host-scripts/. Figure out what runs it
and how often. Then think about what you can write into it.
Output needs to go somewhere you can read from inside the container.
